    "While continued LLM training in the face of distribution shifts is an open problem that few medical institutions possess the resources to handle, updating a knowledge graph with new medications and procedures is relatively straightforward, and the addition or removal of graph components is a constant time operation.",
    "Centralized organization or computer-aided approaches may ameliorate some maintenance issues, and bespoke knowledge graphs compiled from electronic health records 59 raise the possibility of tailoring our defensive technique to institutions.",
